  "text": "In fact, SiO 2(s) is an even more efficient diffusion barrier and the solid  liquid phase change (at T ≈ 1750 K ± 75 K [CITATION_1] ) is endothermic, thus, leading to a reduced net heat flow received by the material and finally to a reduced ablation.",
